Summaries

five sample summaries

[1] She was born into a family who have many colours of skin. Her father’s skin color is bark chocolate.And her grandmother’s skin color is white. Her grandfather’s skin color is yogurt between vanilla and strawberry. She thought it was normal but it wasn’t .She often saw as a prostitute or slave. And she thought it was unnatural that one's skin color is only one skin color. She became a photographer and she started the project to show various skin colors. This is called HUmanae. Take pictures of skins and paint backgrounds to match their skin’s color. More than three thousand people copolated her project,there were both the students of Switzerland and the people who were from poor families .Her work is displayed in many places such as public spaces,streets,and museums. Skin’s color is not only one, there are many differences.
[2] Each of her family members has a different color, so she had never been important to her. But on the outside, color has a lot of meanings. After she got married she was concerned about the color of children, so she worked as a photographer and made Humanae. The posters about it were spread and fostered popular debate and created a community. More than 3000 people all over the world joined it. Humanae makes us rethink how we see each other. Humanae was chosen for the cover of foreign affairs. It is also used by teachers for education. All the frustration, fear, loneliness that she has felt became rough, she said. And she thinks we still need to work hard to abolish discrimination.                                                                                                                                                  
[3] She was born in a family full of colors, so the color of skin was never important for her. However, outside home, things are different soon. The color of skin had many other meanings. With her skin color and hai, she cannot belong to some places. The color of black skin not only gives a first impression. It is her work in progress from a personal story to a global history. She portrays the subjects in a white background. Then she chooses an 11-pixel square from the nose, paints the background, and looks for the corresponding color in the industrial palette, Pantone.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
[4] We live in a world where our impressions are determined by the color of our skin. Angelica grew up in a multi-skinned household. There are people with porcelain white skin, dark chocolate skin, peanut skin, and more. Because of this upbringing , skin color didn’t matter to her. One day, in art class, She was surprised to see that there was only one color, orange. And because of her dark skin, She was called a maid or a prostitute and was treated badly. A few years later, She started a new project as a photographer. With the help of over 3000 people, we are documenting photos of people of all skin colours. Through this project, she realized she could feel confident about her skin color and turn the conflict, fear and loneliness she once fell into love. She said that this project will help many people around the world.      
[5] Angelica’s family is full of color skin, so she thought color was never important,but outside home, she noticed it was different. She was discriminated. Years later, she started existing as a photographer, Humanae. She took picture more than 3000 people around the world. There was a huge response,and this project finds a new life ina different variety of fields.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
5 Levels: Angelica’s family is full of color skin, so she thought color was never important,but outside home, she noticed it was different. She was discriminated. Years later, she started existing as a photographer, Humanae. She took picture more than 3000 people around the world. There was a huge response,and this project finds a new life ina different variety of fields. ...
